d'Alembert sur les spectacles, 1758); ciononostante A. rimase in buoni rapporti con Rousseau fino al 1765. Dal 1746 intrattenne scambi epistolari con i matematici ginevrini Gabriel Cramer e Georges-Louis Le Sage, con lo scienziato basilese Leonhard Euler e con il vodese Henri-Alexandre de Catt, lettore di Federico II di Prussia."]], "wiki_links": [{"item": "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q153232", "itemLabel": "Jean Le Rond d'Alembert", "dhsid": "032402", "namefr": "Jean Le Rond d'Alembert", "articlefr": "https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Le_Rond_d%27Alembert", "namede": "Jean-Baptiste le Rond d\u2019Alembert", "articlede": "https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Baptiste_le_Rond_d%E2%80%99Alembert", "nameit": "Jean Baptiste Le Rond d'Alembert", "articleit": "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Baptiste_Le_Rond_d%27Alembert", "nameen": "Jean le Rond d'Alembert", "articleen": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_le_Rond_d%27Alembert", "instanceof": "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q5", "instanceofLabel": "\u00eatre humain", "gndid": "11850178X"}], "wikidata_url": "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q153232", "wikipedia_page_title": "Jean Baptiste Le Rond d'Alembert", "added_wikidata_wikipedia_to_text_links": true, "_initial": "A", "url": "https://hls-dhs-dss.ch/it/articles/032402/2001-05-22"}